Okay. As briefly as possible. Dungeons & Dragons or the other role-playing games are a game where a group of people get together and one of them devises the kind of skeleton outline of a story in Dungeons & Dragons.
It would be a story about fabulous treasure or a monster in a cave or in a dungeon or something like that. And the other people, each one of them takes the part of a single adventurer.

And in Dungeons & Dragons you can be an elf or a dwarf or a hobbit or a wizard or a hero. And then they pretend to go into the story and try and solve the mystery or find the treasure or whatever, and they all sit around the table and do this and they decide how things come out if they have to decide how an event occurs by just rolling dice and consulting a table in the book to see how the things occur.
So it's a story that's built up by a group of friends working together between them. That's what it is really.
